Description:
------------

netloc_reader_static processes data from a key/value file allowing the user to
create a custom network topology when a netloc reader for their network either
does not exist (yet) or cannot be run.

The resulting .ndat files are used as abstract representations of the
network graph for the netloc API.


Command Line Interface:
-----------------------

--input | -i <input file>              (Required)
   The input JSON file to process.

--outdir | -o <output directory>       (Optional)
   Path to directory where output .dat filess are placed by the tool.
   Default: "./"

--progress | -p                        (Optional)
   Display progress while processing the file.

--help | -h                   (Optional)
   Display a help message.


Examples:
---------

shell$ ./netloc_reader_static -i example-2-nodes.json
